      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/53",
      "text": [
        " : \"لاَ تَأْكُلَنَّ مِنْ فَرِيسَةِ اَلسَّبُعِ وَ لاَ اَلْمَوْقُوذَةِ وَ لاَ اَلْمُنْخَنِقَةِ وَ لاَ اَلْمُتَرَدِّيَةِ وَ لاَ اَلنَّطِيحَةِ إِلاَّ أَنْ تُدْرِكَهُ حَيّاً فَتُذَكِّيَهُ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4173 - Ali ibn Abi Hamzah narrated from Abu Basir, from Abu Abdillah (as), who said:\n\"Do not eat from what has been killed by a predator, nor from that which has been beaten to death, strangled, fallen from a height, or gored, unless you find it alive and slaughter it properly.\""
        ]
      }
    },
